1. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing): The paper deals with workload allocation in a distributed cloud/edge/device computing environment, which falls under the scope of this sub-category. 
2. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper focuses on optimizing AI-workload allocation in emergency medical applications, which involves the use of AI algorithms and techniques. 
3. cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science): The paper applies workload allocation methods to healthcare AI applications, which can be considered as a form of computational science. 
4. cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction): The paper deals with emergency medical applications, which involve interactions between humans (medical staff) and computers (AI systems). 
5. cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper proposes an efficient scheduling and allocation strategy for optimizing system performance in a hierarchical cloud/edge/device computing environment.
